Gold Pouch Deployment Checklist (GitHub Pages)

To launch your affiliate marketing website on GitHub Pages, follow these steps:

Pre-Deployment Verification

[ ] Review index.html to ensure all custom links and asset texts represent your specific affiliate products correctly.

[ ] Verify that the E-Commerce section correctly sits above the Blog section (Verified in code).

[ ] Ensure the white/gold theme looks good across devices (Mobile responsiveness is built-in via Tailwind).

Repository Setup

[ ] Create a new public repository on GitHub (e.g., gold-pouch-web).

[ ] Add the single index.html file to the root of your repository.
(Note: Due to our optimized Single-Page App architecture, the CSS and JS are bundled into this file to minimize requests and prevent rendering-blocking delays).

[ ] Add the generated Markdown files to the repository root for documentation purposes.

Enabling GitHub Pages

[ ] Navigate to the repository Settings tab.

[ ] Click on Pages in the left sidebar.

[ ] Under "Build and deployment", set the Source to Deploy from a branch.

[ ] Under Branch, select main (or master) and keep the folder as / (root).

[ ] Click Save.

Final Checks

[ ] Wait 1-3 minutes for the GitHub Actions deployment pipeline to finish.

[ ] Visit your published URL (e.g., https://yourusername.github.io/gold-pouch-web/).

[ ] Test the popups (E-commerce and Blog) to ensure they open and you can scroll the main page underneath.

[ ] Test the 404 router by manually typing a fake hash at the end of the URL (e.g., index.html#does-not-exist).
